        "title": "(아/어/여 야)되다/하다 (must do,should do)",
        "content": [
            {
                "title": "When we want to say should or must do something, we conjugate korean verbs by changing the verb into its past/present form (using the 아/어/여 conjugations) and adding '야 하다/되다' to the end.",
                "details": "Whether the ending is 야 해요 or 야 돼요 doesn't matter that much, they mean the same."
            }
        ],
